<br>
And it's true that a lot of people badmouth rangers.  But the truth is also that, they are fools.  A guildmate who was NOT a ranger once put it very well when he said &quot;Rangers are a deciptevily poweful class&quot;.  Aside from the fact that their heals suck, they get pretty much all useful spells a druid gets, and then some.  No, their DDs are not up to par, but hell, that's why they've got weapons in both hands.<br>
<br>
No, they dont get warrior HPs, but they get a pretty decent handful of em.  And in truth, rangers can really whack the shit out of stuff when it really comes down to it. And truth be told, if they need to, they can take the hits as well.  Granted, not as well as a warrior in either cases, but if your cleric is getting the crap beat out of them, the warrior doesn't save the cleric with the Greater Heal, the ranger does.  <br>
<br>
And I do reiterate that their heals suck, but it can really make the difference when the casters in the group get low and the cleric has to keep the tank healed.  Any ranger worth his/her shit knows their spells and can relatively masterfully keep themselves in a position out of harm's way and truly contribute in group situations by beating the crap out of mobs whilst a warrior takes the hits (Provided that is possible).  And if not, they can work almost as well.<br>
<br>
If I had a warrior in my group and saw a ranger LFG, I wouldnt hesitate to take the ranger.  And if I couldnt find a warrior, I wouldnt put using the ranger as a tank out of my mind.  So all the l33t &quot;rangers sux0rs&quot; people can kiss my a** ;P<br>
<br>
[Though I do reiterate, anyone who thinks that a class with the current ability of rangers deserves ports as well is a moron] <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utildares.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TildareS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/20/01 5:01:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=598.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ranger's Life isn't Fair (serious read) :*(</span><hr size=1>  B4 you start to talk abought how hard the life of a Ranger is plz try  /ooc Lv 56 Necro looking for party! in Sebelis ore Velk.<br>
<br>
 Ones I was in sebelis for 28h and I was in 1!! yes 1 party that lasted for 1.5 h. (Yes I know I could have moved but I was semi afk time to time, but allways looking if someone would inv me)<br>
<br>
 One thing I think players are missunderstanding is that Necros mabey not are the Uber raide Class but in exp partys they are realy good.<br>
<br>
 In a exp party we bring:<br>
<br>
1 pet (well a pet hitting 59x4 and kick 71 isnt so bad.)<br>
1 mini mess (All &quot;well&quot; played necs can hold 3 Mobs messed)<br>
1 Mini Heal (500 Hps over 24 isnt so bad)<br>
1 Mini Nuke( Well 500DD is mini)<br>
1 Good Dbuff (STR -50 AC -21 and 1000 DoT) <br>
1 Good Snare (70% Snare 1600 DoT)<br>
Nec will never go OOM.<br>
Nec will speed up the party by pumping mana in Healer.<br>
You don't have to Heal em mutch.<br>
And if you get wiped, well the chans that the nec will live is like 90%. Then he just gate and start Summoning Corpse.<br>
<br>
<br>
 So next time you se a nec by zone LFG inv him and try the class out. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
